kinship diagram for anthroplogy using MetaPost

file:     kinship.mp 
version:  alpha state
author:   Dohyun Kim
license:  public domain

usage example:

	beginfig(0);
	u:=2nodesize;
	%%% define members
	male.ego(black); female.mom(black); female.sister(black);
	female.wife(white); male.son(white); female.niece(black);
	male.nephew(black); male.grandson(black);
	%%% fix positions
	lefttoright(wife,ego,sister); lefttoright(son,niece,nephew);
	toppairtobottom(wife,ego,son); toppairtobottom(son,niece,grandson);
	bottompairtotop(ego,sister,mom);
	%%% draw and/or fill
	linktochildren(mom,ego,sister); linktochildren(sister,niece,nephew);
	linkmarriageandchild(ego,wife,son); linkmarriageandchild(son,niece,grandson);
	drawmembers(mom,ego,sister,niece,nephew,wife,son,grandson);
	labelmembers.bot(ego,nephew,grandson);
	endfig;

[N.B] one "ego" is (almost) always required.
